OL,3,CAmbulance service declares critical
OL,4,Cincident after surge in emergency calls
OL,6,FSouth Central Ambulance Service (SCAS)
OL,7,Fdeclared a critical incident after a
OL,8,Fsurge in 999 calls needing an
OL,9,Femergency response.
OL,11,FSCAS said 70% of callers were assessed
OL,12,Fas being in the two most urgent
OL,13,Fcategories, which was higher than
OL,14,Fexpected.
OL,16,FIn a statement, the service said: "We
OL,17,Fdeclared a critical incident yesterday
OL,18,F(Tuesday) afternoon (16:20) primarily
OL,19,Fdue to an increase in the acuity of
OL,20,Fpatients calling 999.
