OL,3,CAmbulance service declares critical
OL,4,Cincident after surge in emergency calls
OL,6,FDeclaring a critical incident means
OL,7,Fthe ambulance service is able to focus
OL,8,Fits resources on those patients most
OL,9,Fin need and highlights the pressures
OL,10,Fthey are experiencing to patients and
OL,11,Fhealth system partners who can provide
OL,12,Fsupport where possible.
OL,14,FThe trust, which covers Berkshire,
OL,15,FBuckinghamshire, Hampshire and
OL,16,FOxfordshire, appealed to patients to
OL,17,Fcall NHS 111 for urgent medical advice
OL,18,Fand guidance wherever possible and
OL,19,Fappropriate to do so, as well as
OL,20,Furgent treatment centres, pharmacists,
OL,21,Fand their GPs.
